6. MEMBERS OF PARLIAMENT RAISING THEIR HANDS STORY :  Somali parliamentarians in Mogadishu voted unanimously on Saturday  ( April 18 )  to implement Sharia law in the country .
Sharia was already in use in areas under control of Islamists and the move is hoped to restore stability and security in Somalia.     Experts say the move to establish sharia or Islamic law is aimed at undermining Islamist guerrillas who have waged an insurgency for the last two years .
A new president ,  prime minister and members of parliament were elected in January under a U.N.-brokered reconciliation process that is Somalia's 15th attempt to set up central government since 1991 .
Macedonia I wrote on 3 April about the situation in Macedonia.  I have just heard some good news from Filip Stojanovski who writes :  Good news :  the Constitutional Court finally ,  after months of deliberation ,  abolished religious instruction within the public education system yesterday .
The curriculum included praying ,  while the implementation generally herded the kids of a certain heritage regardless of the wishes of their parents ,  and fomented various kinds of divisive tendencies on all levels of society .
It's a temporary victory for secularism ,  I foresee a bumpy road ahead because the current  ( right wing ,  clerically minded )  administration gained almost absolute control of all governmental posts ,  including those influencing the composition of this Court .
But at least we can enjoy the here and now ,  for a moment .
